  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, discarding uniformly aneuploid embryos is unlikely to have a meaningful impact on cumulative live birth rates, especially in women over 35 years of age where it is more likely to be employed 98.",
    "As modern invasive techniques still bring technical and financial challenges, non-invasive AIdriven PGT-A could offer the benefits of PGT-A without embryo manipulation and biopsy.",
    "Recent single-center studies have shown ongoing validation of AI models feeding time-lapse imaging data into CNNs to predict ploidy status from abnormal morphokinetic patterns with good accuracy 99, 100.",
    "These models may not replace PGT-A but highlight the potential for PGT-A triage and well-informed guidance towards embryo selection in a noninvasive manner [99] [100] [101] [102].",
    "Once again, further validation and large multi-center datasets must be compiled for standardization and generalization of these AI-driven models."
  ],
